page.title: 10MORDIFORD WILDLIFE
page.content: { VEGETATION This D-Block area includes natural woodland, riverside meadows, arable farmland and fruit orchards. The main trees types are deciduous and include ash, and willows which flourish on the moist flood plain of the river. { WILDLIFE Many animals including deer,roam through the woodlands. There are a wide variety of birds that feed on the abundant insects life. (Haugh wood is also well known for the fossils that can be found there.) {RIVER LIFE The tree lined river banks and reed beds provide habitats for wildfowl and other water birds including Herons, Coots and Swans.
